message.content: cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.HC. The paper discusses the development of a new system for journal classification based on aggregated journal-journal citation data. This is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, since the paper does not focus specifically on any of these sub-categories, it is difficult to determine a single most likely category.
